-- Indian Oil Share Sale May Help Government Raise $4.3 Billion, Bose Says
-- B y   K a r t i k   G o y a l   a n d   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2010-10-19T07:21:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/indian-oil-share-sale-may-help-government-raise-4-3-billion-bose-says.html
A sale of stake in state-owned
Indian Oil Corp. may help the government raise 190 billion
rupees, Disinvestment Secretary Sumit Bose told reporters in New
Delhi today. The government plans to sell stakes in seven more
companies in the year to March 31, with Indian Oil and Oil &
Natural Gas Corp. slated for the last quarter, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartik Goyal in New Delhi at 
 kgoyal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
